name=Player Model Reload Utility
id=PlayerModelReloadUtil
description=Keeps your character visible through the B42 invisible-character bug without reloading your save. In some spots - most often after moving between a basement and the floor above - the engine forces your character's per-player render alpha to 0 and re-asserts it every frame, so you go invisible but stay fully functional. (Diagnostics caught the stuck state on open ground with nothing overhead, so the exact trigger is unconfirmed - it is NOT simply "behind a wall"; the fix works either way.) Auto-Visibility (default ON) re-asserts full alpha every frame so you can't be held invisible - hands-free. A manual Reload (keybind default INSERT, or right-click > Utilities > Reload Player Model) also rebuilds model data for a rarer null-mesh glitch. Optional read-only Visibility Diagnostics (off by default) logs alpha state for debugging. Only changes rendering, never the world/grid, so it can't affect your position. Standalone, no dependencies, load order irrelevant. Safe to remove.
modversion=1.2.0
